# Template for a local, gitignored `.env` to opt into stable local code signing.
#
# NOTE: cli.swift does NOT read this file — loading it into the environment is
# your shell's job. Use direnv (`direnv allow`), or source it yourself
# (`set -a; source .env; set +a`), or just export the variable in your profile.
# cli.swift only reads CHROMIUMKIT_SIGN_IDENTITY from the environment.
#
# Why: the example app is ad-hoc signed by default, so every rebuild gets a new
# code identity and macOS re-prompts for the XCTest automation/accessibility
# grant every time. Signing with a stable identity makes that grant persist.
#
# Create the identity once with:  scripts/make-signing-identity.sh
# See documents/code-signing.md.

# CHROMIUMKIT_SIGN_IDENTITY="ChromiumKit Local"
